hose. Blah, I need some real clarification here lol<br>
<br>
Dutch Grayfist<br>
40 Monk  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uctiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ctiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Loading Please Wait....</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/22/01 4:59:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monkly equipment advice needed</span><hr size=1> First priority should be haste in my opinion.  What I would do is sell your Wu's stick and purchase a FBSS.  Then go camp or purchase a Fighting Baton.  Then you would have haste, Fighting baton in primary and CoT in offhand.<br>
<br>
Wu's stick + CoT (no haste) does pretty much the same as CoT + Lvl 40 bare fist (FBSS).  Fighting Baton + CoT (FBSS) does about 120 more damage a minute than either of the previous two combinations at your lvl.<br>
<br>
Here is a link to Copeland's Damage Calculator.  It is not perfect, but gives a general idea of Damage per Minute, using different combos of weapons and haste.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/copelandeq/weaponanalyzer.html">www.geocities.com/copelan...lyzer.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uqienchi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>qienchi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/22/01 6:33:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monkly equipment advice needed</span><hr size=1> Wu Trance Stick will outdamage your fist even at lvl 60 (unless you have epic) (14/26 vs 7/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I don't really understand what you're trying to do. Reducing your damage to reduce aggro is just silly, the faster the monster go down the better, even if that means you take a little bit of beating. If you want to reduce aggro then all you need to do is FD for a bit. I think FD is abit bugged again now though (doesn't memwipe properly).Also I think the major reason why Wu attracts so much aggro is the proc. <br>
<br>
But anyway, put it this way, you're a lvl 40 monk with a 7/18 weapon. Average warriors (even twinked) won't be able to outdamage you, so IMO you just have to live with that aggro and learn to manage it. <br>
<br>
Btw, how much does SoS go for now that Chardok is busier? I think they still cost ALOT. <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukracs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kracs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/22/01 4:15:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monkly equipment advice needed</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't worry too much about reducing agro at your lvl, really only epic encounters (dragons etc...) or places like the shroom/reet area in sebilis where ya want to keep the agro on the main tank.<br>
<br>
If you're really worried about the issue, or your healers complaining, either stop attacking or feign out for a few seconds and make sure your main tank IS taunting. A SK (and to a lesser degree pally) played well should keep agro off you using both taunt and spells. A warrior has to rely on his taunt button and dmg though so may have problems taunting off a monk weilding low delay weapons.<br>
<br>
You can always go to 2HB, hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , though you gotta watch out for which one you choose as my Tranquil Staff taunts better than me epic fists <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
